useful <- c(
    "YouTube search",
    "Browse features",
    "Channel pages",
    "Suggested videos",
    "External")

wViewsDate <- ViewsDate |>
    pivot_wider(id_cols = Date,
                names_from = `Traffic source`,
                values_from = Views) |>
    mutate(Total_Views = rowSums(across(where(is.numeric))),
           Others = rowSums(across(!any_of(c(
               useful, "Date", "Total_Views"
           ))))) |>
    select(Date, all_of(useful), Others, Total_Views) |> 
    filter(Total_Views > 0)

wViewsDate |> 
    ggplot() + 
    geom_line(aes(Date, Total_Views)) +
    labs(
        title = "Number of Views per Day across time",
        x = "Date",
        y = "Views",
        subtitle = "Redlines are IPMAT Indore exam days",
        color = NULL
    ) +
    geom_vline(
        xintercept = exam_dates$Indore,
        color = "firebrick",
        linetype = "dashed")

The red lines are dates of IPM exams.

wViewsDate |> 
    select(!Total_Views) |> 
    pivot_longer(
        cols = !Date, 
        names_to = "Traffic_Source", 
        values_to = "Views") |> 
    mutate(isYT = (Traffic_Source == "YouTube search")) |>
        ggplot() + 
    geom_line(
        aes(
            Date, 
            `Views`, 
            color = `Traffic_Source`, 
            linetype = isYT
),
        size = 1.1, 
        alpha = 0.75) + 
    scale_color_brewer(palette = "Paired") + 
    scale_linetype_manual(values = c("dashed", "solid"), guide = "none") +
    labs(
        title = "Number of Views per Traffic Source across time",
        subtitle = "Which source generates the most views?",
        x = "Date",
        y = "Views per Day",
        color = NULL
    )  +
    geom_vline(
        xintercept = exam_dates$Indore,
        linetype = "dashed",
        color = "firebrick")

As percentage of total views:

wViewsDate |> 
    mutate(
        across(where(is.numeric), 
               ~ifelse(
                   Total_Views == 0, 0, 
                   ./Total_Views * 100))) -> wpViewsDate


wpViewsDate |>
    select(!Total_Views) |>
    pivot_longer(cols = !Date,
                 names_to = "Traffic_Source",
                 values_to = "%_of_Total_Views") |>
    mutate(isYT = (Traffic_Source == "YouTube search")) |>
    ggplot(aes(Date,
               `%_of_Total_Views`,
               color = `Traffic_Source`)) +
    geom_line(aes(linetype = isYT,), 
              size = 1.1,
              alpha = 0.75) +
    scale_color_brewer(palette = "Paired") +
    scale_linetype_manual(values = c("dashed", "solid"),
                          guide = "none") +
    labs(
        title = "% of daily views per Traffic Source across time.",
        subtitle = "Which source comprises most of total views?",
        y = "Percentage of Total Views",
        color = NULL)  +
    geom_vline(
        xintercept = exam_dates$Indore,
        color = "firebrick",
        linetype = "dashed")

wpViewsDate |> 
    select(!Total_Views) |> 
    pivot_longer(
        cols = !Date, 
        names_to = "Traffic_Source", 
        values_to = "%_of_Total_Views") |> 
    ggplot(aes(Date, `%_of_Total_Views`)) + 
    geom_line() + facet_wrap(~`Traffic_Source`, 
                             strip.position = "top") +
    labs(
        title = "Percentage of Views vs. Sources across time",
        subtitle = "Which source comprises most of total views?",
        x = "",
        y = "Percentage of Total Views"
    )

what to do? Seriously

according to Claude these are the categories:

    Based on the video titles provided, here are 5 potential categories to group these YouTube videos:

1. IPMAT Preparation and Strategy
This category would include videos focused on tips, preparation strategies, analysis etc. for the IPMAT exam specifically. Example video titles: "Study Plan for IPMAT 2021 by Topper", "How to prepare for IPMAT from scratch, after boards?"

2. Life at IIM as an IPM Student 
This category would cover day-in-the-life videos, campus tours, hostel tours etc related to the IPM programs at different IIMs. Example titles: "IIM Indore Campus Tour", "IIM Rohtak - IPM Student Room Tour"

3. IPM Faculty and Student Interviews/Discussions
This category would have conversations, interviews with IPM professors, students sharing their experiences and insights. Example titles: "IIM Indore Faculty on Ideal IPM Student", "IPMAT IIM Indore AIR 2 Topper Interview"  

4. Updates on New IPM Programs  
This category would cover latest announcements, details regarding new IPM programs at institutes like IIM Bodhgaya, IIM Ranchi etc. Example title: "IIM JAMMU launching the IPM Programme in 2021!"

5. Section-wise Prep for Quantitative and Verbal Ability  
This category would have specific lectures/tips to prepare for different sections like quant, logical reasoning, verbal ability for IPMAT. Example titles: "How to prepare for Quantitative Ability - IPMAT 2022/23", "ParaJumbles | IPMAT,DUJAT, XAT,SET,CUET,NPAT"

Let me know if you need any other suggestions for potential categories!
